#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:74
msgid "Other methods"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:76
msgid "There are many other methods. Some of them rely on the physics of stars, such as the relationship between luminosity and color for various types of stars (this is usually represented on a *Hertzsprung-Russel Diagram*). Some of them work for star clusters, such as the *Moving cluster method* and the *main-sequence fitting method*. The *Tully-Fisher relation* that relates the brightness of a spiral galaxy to its rotation can be used to find the distance modulus, since the rotation of a galaxy is easy to measure using *Doppler shift*. Distances to distant galaxies may be found by measuring the *Cosmological redshift*, which is the redshift of light from distance galaxies that results from the expansion of the universe."
msgstr ""

